senses.sense_definition: Any primitive chordate animal belonging to the phyla Hemichordata, Urochordata, or Cephalochordata, which lacks a true vertebral column.

examples.text: Biologists examine the anatomy of the <w>protochordate</w> to understand the evolutionary transition to vertebrates.
The lancelet is a well-known marine <w>protochordate</w> that spends much of its time buried in sand.
